The paper deals with the problem of recovering a high-dimensional structured signal from quantized linear measurements, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), multimedia (cs.MM), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper specifically focuses on linear approaches to signal recovery, which is a topic of interest in all of these sub-categories.
